#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:622
#, no-c-format
msgid "MD RAID on multipath devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:623
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"MD RAID arrays on top of multipathing are set up automatically by the "
"system's udev rules. No special configuration in <filename>/etc/mdadm.conf</"
"filename> is necessary."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:631
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>multipathd</command> daemon and the <command>multipath</"
"command> command"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:632
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>multipathd</command> is the most important part of a modern Linux "
"device mapper multipath setup. It is normally started through the systemd "
"service <filename>multipathd.service</filename> . Socket activation via "
"<filename>multipathd.socket</filename> is supported, but it's "
"<emphasis>strongly recommended</emphasis> to enable <filename>multipathd."
"service</filename> on systems with multipath hardware."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:640
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>multipathd</command> serves the following tasks (some of them "
"depend on the configuration):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:646
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t On startup, detects path devices and sets up multipath maps from\t "
"detected devices.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:652
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Monitors uevents and device mapper events, adding or removing path\t "
"mappings to multipath maps as necessary and initiating failover or\t "
"failback operations.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:659
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Sets up new maps on the fly when new path devices are discovered.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Checks path devices at regular intervals to detect failure, and\t tests "
"failed paths to reinstate them if they become operational\t again.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:671
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t When all paths fail, <command>multipathd</command> either fails the map, "
"or switches the map\t device to queuing mode for a given time interval.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:677
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Handles path state changes and switches path groups or regroups\t paths, "
"as necessary.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:683
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Tests paths for &ldquo;marginal&rdquo; state, i.e. shaky fabrics\t "
"conditions that cause path state flipping between operational and\t non-"
"operational.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:690
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Handles SCSI persistent reservation keys for path devices \t if "
"configured. See\t <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-mpiotools-mpathpersist\" "
"xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> .\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:698
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>multipathd</command> also serves as a command line client to "
"process interactive commands by sending them to the running daemon. The "
"general syntax to send commands to the daemon is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:703
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipathd <replaceable>COMMAND</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:704
#, no-c-format
msgid "or"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:707
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipathd -k\"<replaceable>COMMAND</replaceable>\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:708
#, no-c-format
msgid "To enter the interactive mode with the daemon, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:711
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipathd -k"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:713
#, no-c-format
msgid "How multipath and multipathd work together"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Many <command>multipathd</command> commands have\t <command>multipath</"
"command> equivalents. For example,\t <command>multipathd show topology</"
"command> does the same\t thing as <command>multipath -ll</command> . The "
"notable difference is\t that the multipathd command inquires the internal "
"state of the running\t <command>multipathd</command> daemon, whereas "
"multipath obtains\t information directly from the kernel and I/O operations."
"\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:723
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t If the multipath daemon is running, it is recommended to make\t "
"modifications to the system by using the\t <command>multipathd</command> "
"commands. Otherwise, the daemon may\t notice configuration changes and react "
"to them. In some situations,\t the daemon might even try to undo the applied "
"changes. Therefore,\t <command>multipath</command> \t automatically "
"delegates certain possibly dangerous commands, like\t destroying and "
"flushing maps, to <command>multipathd</command> if\t a running daemon is "
"detected.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:735
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The list bellow describes frequently used <command>multipathd</command> "
"commands:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:738
#, no-c-format
msgid "show topology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:740
#, no-c-format
msgid "\tShows the current map topology and properties."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:746
#, no-c-format
msgid "show paths"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:748
#, no-c-format
msgid "\tShows the currently known path devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:754
#, no-c-format
msgid "show paths format \" <replaceable>FORMAT STRING</replaceable> \""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:756
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tShows the currently known path devices using a format string. Use\t "
"<command>show wildcards</command> to see a list of supported format "
"specifiers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:763
#, no-c-format
msgid "show maps"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:765
#, no-c-format
msgid "\tShows the currently configured map devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:771
#, no-c-format
msgid "show maps format <replaceable>FORMAT STRING</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:773
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tShows the currently configured map devices using a format string. Use\t "
"<command>show wildcards</command> to see a list of supported format "
"specifiers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:780
#, no-c-format
msgid "show config local"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:782
#, no-c-format
msgid "\tShows the current configuration that multipathd is using."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:788
#, no-c-format
msgid "reconfigure"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:790
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tReread configuration files, rescan devices, and set up maps\tagain. This "
"is basically equivalent to a restart of\t <command>multipathd</command> . A "
"few options cannot be modified\twithout a restart. They are mentioned in the "
"man page\t <systemitem>multipath.conf(5)</systemitem> . The\t "
"<option>reconfigure</option> command reloads only map devices that\thave "
"changed in some way. To force reloading every map device, use\t "
"<command>reconfigure all</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:803
#, no-c-format
msgid "del map <replaceable>MAP DEVICE NAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:805
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tUnconfigure and delete the given map device and its partitions.\t "
"<replaceable>MAP DEVICE NAME</replaceable> can be a device node name like\t "
"<filename>dm-0</filename> , a WWID, or a map name. The command fails if\tthe "
"device is in use."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:814
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additional commands are available to modify path states, enable or disable "
"queueing, and more. See <systemitem>multipathd(8)</systemitem> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:821
#, no-c-format
msgid "The multipath command"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:822
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Even though multipath setup is mostly automatic and handled by "
"<command>multipathd</command> , <command>multipath</command> is still useful "
"for some administration tasks. Several examples of the command usage follow:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:830
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:832
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detects path devices and configures all multipath maps that it finds."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:838
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -d"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:840
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tSimilar to <command>multipath</command> , but does not set up\tany maps "
"(&ldquo;dry run&rdquo;)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:847
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:849
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configures a specific multipath device. <replaceable>DEVICENAME</"
"replaceable> can denote a member path device by its device node name "
"( <filename>/dev/sdb</filename> ) or device number in <literal>major:minor</"
"literal> format. Alternatively, it can be the WWID or name of a multipath "
"map."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:859
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -f <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:861
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tUnconfigures (\"flushes\") a multipath map and its partition mappings."
"\tThe command will fail if the map or one of its partitions is in use.\tSee "
"above for possible values of <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:869
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -F"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tUnconfigures (\"flushes\") all multipath maps and their partition mappings."
"\tThe command will fail for maps in use."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:878
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -ll"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:880
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tDisplays the status and topology of all currently configured multipath"
"\tdevices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:887
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -ll <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:889
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Displays the status of a specified multipath device. See above for possible "
"values of <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:896
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:898
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows the internal hardware table and the active configuration of multipath. "
"Refer to <systemitem>multipath.conf(5)</systemitem> for details about the "
"configuration parameters."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:907
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -T"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:909
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tHas a similar function as the <command>multipath -t</command> command\tbut "
"shows only hardware entries for the hardware detected on the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:916
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The option <option>-v</option> controls the verbosity of the output. You can "
"use values between 0 (only fatal errors) and 4 (verbose logging). The "
"default is <option>-v2</option> . The <option>verbosity</option> option in "
"<filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> can be used to change the default "
"verbosity for both <command>multipath</command> and <command>multipathd</"
"command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:926
#, no-c-format
msgid "The mpathpersist utility"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:927
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>mpathpersist</command> utility is used to manage SCSI "
"persistent reservations on Device Mapper Multipath devices. Persistent "
"reservations serve to restrict access to SCSI Logical Units to certain SCSI "
"initiators. In multipath configurations, it is important to use the same "
"reservation keys for all I_T nexuses (paths) for a given volume; otherwise, "
"creating a reservation on one path may cause other paths to fail."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:935
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use this utility with the <literal>reservation_key</literal> attribute in "
"the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file to set persistent "
"reservations for SCSI devices. If (and only if) this option is set, the "
"<command>multipathd</command> daemon checks persistent reservations for "
"newly discovered paths or reinstated paths."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:942
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can add the attribute to the <literal>defaults</literal> section or the "
"<literal>multipaths</literal> section of <filename>multipath.conf</"
"filename> . For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:948
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"multipaths {\n"
"    multipath {\n"
"        wwid             3600140508dbcf02acb448188d73ec97d\n"
"        alias            yellow\n"
"        reservation_key  0x123abc\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:955
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After setting <literal>reservation_key</literal> parameter for all mpath "
"devices applicable for persistent management, reload the configuration using "
"<command>multipathd reconfigure</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:961
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &ldquo; <option>reservation_key file</option> &rdquo;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:964
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the special value <literal>reservation_key file</literal> is used in the "
"<literal>defaults</literal> section of <filename>multipath.conf</filename> , "
"reservation keys can be managed dynamically in the file <filename>/etc/"
"multipath/prkeys</filename> using <command>mpathpersist</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:971
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the recommended way to handle persistent reservations with multipath "
"maps. It is available from &productname; 12 SP4."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:976
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the command <command>mpathpersist</command> to query and set persistent "
"reservations for multipath maps consisting of SCSI devices. Refer to the "
"manual page <systemitem>mpathpersist(8)</systemitem> for details. The "
"command line options are the same as those of the <command>sg_persist</"
"command> from the <systemitem>sg3_utils</systemitem> package. The "
"<systemitem>sg_persist(8)</systemitem> manual page explains the semantics of "
"the options in detail."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:987
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the following examples, <replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable> denotes a "
"device mapper multipath device like <filename>/dev/mapper/mpatha</"
"filename> . The commands below are listed with long options for better "
"readability. All options have single-letter replacements, like in "
"<command>mpathpersist -oGS 123abc <replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable></"
"command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:997
#, no-c-format
msgid "mpathpersist --in --read-keys <replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:999
#, no-c-format
msgid "Read the registered reservation keys for the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1005
#, no-c-format
msgid "mpathpersist --in --read-reservation <replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1007
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show existing reservations for the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1013
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mpathpersist --out --register --param-sark=123abc <replaceable>DEVICE</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1015
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Register a reservation key for the device. This will add the reservation key "
"for all I_T nexuses (path devices) on the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1022
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mpathpersist --out --reserve --param-rk=123abc --prout-type=5 "
"<replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1024
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a reservation of type 5 (&ldquo;write exclusive - registrants "
"only&rdquo;) for the device, using the previously registered key."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1032
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mpathpersist --out --release --param-rk=123abc --prout-type=5 "
"<replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1034
#, no-c-format
msgid "Release a reservation of type 5 for the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1040
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mpathpersist --out --register-ignore --param-sark=0 <replaceable>DEVICE</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1042
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Delete a previously existing reservation key from the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1051
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the system for multipathing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1056
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling, starting, and stopping multipath services"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1057
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To enable multipath services to start at boot time, run the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1061
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl enable multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1062
#, no-c-format
msgid "To manually start the service in the running system, enter:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1065
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl start multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1066
#, no-c-format
msgid "To restart the service, enter:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1069
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl restart multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1070
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In most situations, restarting the service is not necessary. To simply have "
"<command>multipathd</command> reload its configuration, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1074
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl reload multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1075
#, no-c-format
msgid "To check the status of the service, enter:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1078
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl status multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1079
#, no-c-format
msgid "To stop the multipath services in the current session, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1082
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.sudo;systemctl stop multipathd\n"
"&prompt.sudo;systemctl stop multipathd.socket\n"
"   "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1087
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disabling multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1088
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is strongly recommended to have <filename>multipathd.service</filename> "
"always enabled and running on every host that has access to multipath "
"hardware. However, sometimes it may be necessary to disable the service "
"because multipath hardware has been removed, because some other multipathing "
"software is going to be deployed, or for troubleshooting purposes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1096
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To disable multipathing <emphasis>just for a single system boot</emphasis> , "
"use the kernel parameter <literal>multipath=off</literal> . This affects "
"both the booted system and the initial ramfs, which does not need to be "
"rebuilt in this case."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To disable multipathd services <emphasis>permanently</emphasis> , so that "
"they will not be started on future system boots, run the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;systemctl disable multipathd\n"
"&prompt.sudo;systemctl disable multipathd.socket\n"
"&prompt.sudo;dracut --force --omit multipath\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"(Whenever you disable or enable the multipath services, rebuild the "
"<systemitem>initrd</systemitem> . See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-initrd-"
"sync\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> .)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additionally and optionally, if you also want to make sure multipath devices "
"do not get set up, even when running <command>multipath</command> manually, "
"add the following lines at the end of <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</"
"filename> before rebuilding the initrd:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"blacklist {\n"
"    wwid .*\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing SAN devices for multipathing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before configuring multipath I/O for your SAN devices, prepare the SAN "
"devices, as necessary, by doing the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure and zone the SAN with the vendor’s tools."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure permissions for host LUNs on the storage arrays with the vendor’s "
"tools."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If &productname; ships no driver for the host bus adapter (HBA), install a "
"Linux driver from the HBA vendor. See the vendor’s specific instructions for "
"more details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1154
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If multipath devices are detected and <filename>multipathd.service</"
"filename> is enabled, multipath maps should be created automatically. If "
"this does not happen, use commands like <command>lsscsi</command> to check "
"the probing of the low-level devices. Also, inspect the system logs with "
"<command>journalctl -b</command> . When the LUNs are not seen by the HBA "
"driver, check the zoning setup in the SAN. In particular, check whether LUN "
"masking is active and whether the LUNs are correctly assigned to the server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the HBA driver can see LUNs, but no corresponding block devices are "
"created, additional kernel parameters may be needed. See <citetitle>TID "
"3955167: Troubleshooting SCSI (LUN) Scanning Issues</citetitle> in the "
"&suse; Knowledgebase at <link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/support/kb/"
"doc.php?id=3955167\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1173
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partitions on multipath devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1174
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multipath maps can have partitions like their path devices. Partition table "
"scanning and device node creation for partitions is done in user space by "
"the <command>kpartx</command> tool. <command>kpartx</command> is "
"automatically invoked by udev rules; there is usually no need to run it "
"manually. Technically, &ldquo;partition&rdquo; devices created by kpartx are "
"also device mapper devices that simply map a linear range of blocks from the "
"parent device. The <replaceable>N</replaceable> th partition of a multipath "
"device with known WWID can be accessed reliably via <filename>/dev/disk/by-"
"id/dm-uuid-part<replaceable>N</replaceable>-mpath-<replaceable>WWID</"
"replaceable></filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1187
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disabling invocation of <command>kpartx</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tThe <literal>skip_kpartx</literal> option in\t <filename>/etc/multipath."
"conf</filename> can be used to disable\tinvocation of <command>kpartx</"
"command> on selected multipath maps. This\tmay be useful on virtualization "
"hosts, for example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1195
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Partition tables and partitions on multipath devices can be manipulated as "
"usual, using &yast; or tools like <command>fdisk</command> or "
"<command>parted</command> . Changes applied to the partition table will be "
"noted by the system when the partitioning tool exits. If this does not work "
"(usually because a device is busy), try <command>multipathd reconfigure</"
"command> , or reboot the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1203
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A partitioned multipath device cannot be used otherwise. For example, you "
"cannot create an LVM physical volume from a partitioned device. You will "
"need to wipe the partition table before doing this."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1211
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1213
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The built-in <systemitem>multipath-tools</systemitem> defaults work well for "
"most setups. If customizations are needed, a configuration file needs to be "
"created. The main configuration file is <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</"
"filename> . In addition, files matching the pattern <filename>/etc/multipath/"
"conf.d/*.conf</filename> are read in alphabetical order. See <xref linkend="
"\"sec-multipath-conf-file-syntax\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> for "
"precedence rules."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1223
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generated configuration files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1226
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The files <filename>/etc/multipath/wwids</filename> , <filename>/etc/"
"multipath/bindings</filename> , and <filename>/etc/multipath/prkeys</"
"filename> are maintained by <systemitem>multipath-tools</systemitem> to "
"store persistent information about previously created multipath maps, map "
"names, and reservation keys for SCSI persistent reservations, respectively. "
"Do not edit these generated configuration files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1238
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configurable paths"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Except for <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> , the paths of the "
"configuration directories and files are configurable, but changing these "
"paths is strongly discouraged."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1247
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating the /etc/multipath.conf file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1248
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can generate a <filename>multipath.conf</filename> template from the "
"built-in defaults. This makes all default settings explicit. The behavior of "
"<systemitem>multipath-tools</systemitem> will not change unless the "
"generated file is modified. To generate the configuration template, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1255
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -T &gt;/etc/multipath.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can create a minimal <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</"
"filename> that just contains those settings you want to change. The behavior "
"will be identical to modifying only the respective lines in the generated "
"template."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1266
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath.conf Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file uses a hierarchy of "
"sections, subsections, and attribute/value pairs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Whitespace separates tokens. Consecutive whitespace characters are\t "
"collapsed into a single space, unless quoted (see below).\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1279
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The hash ( <literal>#</literal> )\t and exclamation mark ( <literal>!</"
"literal> ) characters cause the\t rest of the line to be discarded as a "
"comment.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1286
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Sections and subsections are started with a section name and an opening "
"brace\t ( <literal>{</literal> ) on the same line, and end with a closing\t "
"brace ( <literal>}</literal> ) on a line on its own.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Attributes and values are written on one line. Line continuations\t are "
"unsupported.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Attributes and section names must be keywords. The allowed keywords are\t "
"documented in <systemitem>multipath.conf(5)</systemitem> .\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Values may be enclosed in double quotes ( <literal>\"</literal> ). They\t "
"must be enclosed in quotes if they contain whitespace or comment\t "
"characters. A double quote character inside a value is represented\t by a "
"pair of double quotes ( <literal>\"\"</literal> ).\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The values of some attributes are POSIX regular expressions\t (see "
"<systemitem>regex(7)</systemitem> ). They are case sensitive and\t not "
"anchored, so &ldquo; <literal>bar</literal> &rdquo; matches\t &ldquo; "
"<literal>rhabarber</literal> &rdquo;.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: bridgehead
#: storage_multipath.xml:1321
#, no-c-format
msgid "Syntax Example"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1322
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"section {\n"
"    subsection {\n"
"        attr1 value\n"
"\t   attr2      \"complex value!\"\n"
"\tattr3    \"value with \"\"quoted\"\" word\"\n"
"    } ! subsection end\n"
"} # section end\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: bridgehead
#: storage_multipath.xml:1331
#, no-c-format
msgid "Precedence Rules"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As noted at the beginning of <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-conf-file\" "
"xrefstyle=\"HeadingOnPage\"/> , it is possible to have multiple "
"configuration files. The additional files follow the same syntax rules as "
"<filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> . Sections and attributes can occur "
"multiple times. If the same attribute is set in multiple files, or on "
"multiple lines in the same file, the last value read takes precedence."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1342
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> sections"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1343
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file is organized into the "
"following sections. Some attributes can occur in more than one section. See "
"<systemitem>multipath.conf(5)</systemitem> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1350
#, no-c-format
msgid "defaults"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1352
#, no-c-format
msgid "General default settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1358
#, no-c-format
msgid "blacklist"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Lists devices to ignore. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-blacklist\" "
"xrefstyle=\"HeadingOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1367
#, no-c-format
msgid "blacklist_exceptions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Lists devices to be multipathed even though they are matched by the "
"blacklist. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-blacklist\" xrefstyle="
"\"HeadingOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1377
#, no-c-format
msgid "devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tSettings specific to the storage controller. This section is\ta collection "
"of <literal>device</literal> subsections. Values in this section\toverride "
"values for the same attributes in the\t <filename>defaults</filename> "
"section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1388
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipaths"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tSettings for individual multipath devices. This section is a list of\t "
"<literal>multipath</literal> subsections. Values override\tthe "
"<literal>defaults</literal> and <literal>devices</literal> sections."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1398
#, no-c-format
msgid "overrides"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1400
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Settings that override values from all other sections."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1409
#, no-c-format
msgid "Applying <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> modifications"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1410
#, no-c-format
msgid "To apply the configuration changes, run"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1413
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;multipathd reconfigure"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1414
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do not forget to synchronize with the configuration in the initrd. See <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-multipath-initrd-sync\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1419
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not apply settings using <command>multipath</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1420
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do not apply new settings with the <command>multipath</command> command "
"while <command>multipathd</command> is running. This may result in an "
"inconsistent and possibly broken setup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1427
#, no-c-format
msgid "Verifying a modified setup"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1428
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to test modified settings first before they are applied, by "
"running:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1432
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -d -v2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1433
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This command shows new maps to be created with the proposed topology. "
"However, the command does not show whether maps will be removed/flushed. To "
"obtain even more information, run this command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1438
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -d -v3 2&gt;&amp;1 | less"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1443
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generating a WWID"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1444
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To identify a device over different paths, multipath uses a World Wide "
"Identification (WWID) for each device. If the WWID is the same for two "
"device paths, they are assumed to represent the same device. We recommend "
"not changing the method of WWID generation, unless there is a compelling "
"reason to do so. For more details, see <command>man multipath.conf</"
"command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1455
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring policies for polling, queuing, and failback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1457
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section discusses the most important <systemitem>multipath-tools</"
"systemitem> configuration parameters for achieving fault tolerance."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1464
#, no-c-format
msgid "polling_interval"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1466
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The time interval (in seconds) between health checks for path\t devices. "
"The default is 5 seconds. Failed devices are checked at\t this time "
"interval. For healthy devices, the time interval may be\t increased up to "
"<literal>max_polling_interval</literal> seconds.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1475
#, no-c-format
msgid "no_path_retry"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1477
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Determine what happens if all paths of a given multipath map have\t "
"failed or disappeared. The possible values are:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1483
#, no-c-format
msgid "fail"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1485
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Fail I/O on the multipath map. This will cause I/O errors in\t upper "
"layers such as mounted file systems. The affected\t file systems, and "
"possibly the entire host, will enter\t degraded mode.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1494
#, no-c-format
msgid "queue"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1496
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t I/O on the multipath map is queued in the device-mapper\t layer and sent "
"to the device when path devices become available\t again. This is the safest "
"option to avoid losing data, but it\t can have negative effects if the path "
"devices don't get\t reinstated for a long time. Processes reading from the "
"device\t will hang in uninterruptible sleep\t ( <literal>D</literal> ) state."
"\t Queued data occupies memory, which becomes unavailable\t for processes. "
"Eventually, memory will be exhausted.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1510
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>N</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1512
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t <replaceable>N</replaceable> is a positive integer.\t Keep the map device "
"in queuing mode for <replaceable>N</replaceable> \t polling intervals. When "
"the time elapses, <command>multipathd</command> fails the map\t device. If "
"<literal>polling_interval</literal> is 5 seconds and\t "
"<literal>no_path_retry</literal> is 6,\t <command>multipathd</command> will "
"queue I/O for approximately\t 6 * 5s = 30s before failing I/O on the map "
"device. A carefully chosen\t timeout value is often a good compromise between"
"\t <literal>fail</literal> and <literal>queue</literal> .\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1529
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal of multipath I/O is to provide connectivity fault tolerance between "
"the storage system and the server. The desired default behavior depends on "
"whether the server is a stand-alone server or a node in a high-availability "
"cluster."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1536
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you configure multipath I/O for a stand-alone server, the "
"<literal>no_path_retry</literal> setting protects the server operating "
"system from receiving I/O errors as long as possible. It queues messages "
"until a multipath failover occurs and provides a healthy connection."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1543
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you configure multipath I/O for a node in a high-availability cluster, "
"you want multipath to report the I/O failure to trigger the resource "
"failover instead of waiting for a multipath failover to be resolved. In "
"cluster environments, you must modify the <literal>no_path_retry </literal> "
"setting so that the cluster node receives an I/O error in relation to the "
"cluster verification process (recommended to be 50% of the heartbeat "
"tolerance) if the connection is lost to the storage system. In addition, you "
"want the multipath I/O fallback to be set to manual to avoid a ping-pong of "
"resources because of path failures."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1555
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file should contain a "
"<command>defaults</command> section where you can specify default behaviors "
"for polling, queuing, and failback. If the field is not otherwise specified "
"in a <command>device</command> section, the default setting is applied for "
"that SAN configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1563
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following are the compiled default settings. They will be used unless "
"you overwrite these values by creating and configuring a personalized "
"<filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1569
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"defaults {\n"
"  verbosity 2\n"
"#  udev_dir is deprecated in SLES 11 SP3\n"
"#  udev_dir              /dev\n"
"  polling_interval      5\n"
"#  path_selector default value is service-time in SLES 11 SP3\n"
"#  path_selector         \"round-robin 0\"\n"
"  path selector         \"service-time 0\"\n"
"  path_grouping_policy  failover\n"
"#  getuid_callout is deprecated in SLES 11 SP3 and replaced with "
"uid_attribute\n"
"#  getuid_callout        \"/usr/lib/udev/scsi_id --whitelisted --device=/dev/"
"%n\"\n"
"#  uid_attribute is new in SLES 11 SP3\n"
"  uid_attribute         \"ID_SERIAL\"\n"
"  prio                  \"const\"\n"
"  prio_args             \"\"\n"
"  features              \"0\"\n"
"  path_checker          \"tur\"\n"
"  alias_prefix          \"mpath\"\n"
"  rr_min_io_rq          1\n"
"  max_fds               \"max\"\n"
"  rr_weight             \"uniform\"\n"
"  queue_without_daemon  \"yes\"\n"
"  flush_on_last_del     \"no\"\n"
"  user_friendly_names   \"no\"\n"
"  fast_io_fail_tmo      5\n"
"  bindings_file         \"/etc/multipath/bindings\"\n"
"  wwids_file            \"/etc/multipath/wwids\"\n"
"  log_checker_err       \"always\"\n"
"\n"
"  retain_attached_hw_handler  \"no\"\n"
"  detect_prio           \"no\"\n"
"  failback              \"manual\"\n"
"  no_path_retry         \"fail\"\n"
"  }"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1604
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For information about setting the polling, queuing, and failback policies, "
"see the following parameters in <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-policies-"
"failover\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1612
#, no-c-format
msgid "<xref linkend=\"vle-polling-interval\" xrefstyle=\"HeadingOnPage\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1617
#, no-c-format
msgid "<xref linkend=\"vle-no-path-retry\" xrefstyle=\"HeadingOnPage\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1622
#, no-c-format
msgid "<xref linkend=\"vle-failback\" xrefstyle=\"HeadingOnPage\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1637
#, no-c-format
msgid "Blacklisting non-multipath devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1639
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file can contain a "
"<command>blacklist</command> section where all non-multipath devices are "
"listed. You can blacklist devices by WWID ( <literal>wwid</literal> "
"keyword), device name ( <literal>devnode</literal> keyword), or device type "
"( <literal>device</literal> section). You can also use the "
"<literal>blacklist_exceptions</literal> section to enable multipath for some "
"devices that are blacklisted by the regular expressions used in the "
"<literal>blacklist</literal> section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1651
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preferred blacklisting methods"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1652
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The preferred method for blacklisting devices is by <emphasis>WWID</"
"emphasis> or by <emphasis>vendor and product</emphasis> . Blacklisting by "
"<emphasis>devnode</emphasis> is not recommended, because device nodes can "
"change and thus are not useful for persistent device identification."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1662
#, no-c-format
msgid "Regular expressions in multipath.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1663
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regular expressions in the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> do "
"<emphasis>not</emphasis> work in general. They only work if they are matched "
"against common strings. However, the standard configuration of multipath "
"already contains regular expressions for many devices and vendors. Matching "
"regular expressions with other regular expressions does not work. Make sure "
"that you are only matching against strings shown with <command>multipath -t</"
"command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can typically ignore non-multipathed devices, such as <literal>hpsa</"
"literal> , <literal>fd</literal> , <literal>hd</literal> , <literal>md</"
"literal> , <literal>dm</literal> , <literal>sr</literal> , <literal>scd</"
"literal> , <literal>st</literal> , <literal>ram</literal> , <literal>raw</"
"literal> , and <literal>loop</literal> . For example, local SATA hard disks "
"and flash disks do not have multiple paths. If you want <command>multipath</"
"command> to ignore single-path devices, put them in the <command>blacklist</"
"command> section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1686
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1687
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The keyword <literal>devnode_blacklist</literal> has been deprecated and "
"replaced with the keyword <literal>blacklist</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1691
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With &sls; 12 the glibc-provided regular expressions are used. To match an "
"arbitrary string, you must now use <literal>\".*\"</literal> rather than "
"<literal>\"*\"</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1698
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, to blacklist local devices and all arrays from the "
"<filename>hpsa</filename> driver from being managed by multipath, the "
"<command>blacklist</command> section looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1704
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"blacklist {\n"
"      wwid \"26353900f02796769\"\n"
"      devnode \"^(ram|raw|loop|fd|md|dm-|sr|scd|st)[0-9]*\"\n"
"      devnode \"^sd[a-z][0-9]*\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1710
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also blacklist only the partitions from a driver instead of the "
"entire array. For example, you can use the following regular expression to "
"blacklist only partitions from the cciss driver and not the entire array:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1716
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"blacklist {\n"
"      devnode \"^cciss!c[0-9]d[0-9]*[p[0-9]*]\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1720
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can blacklist by specific device types by adding a <literal>device</"
"literal> section in the blacklist, and using the <literal>vendor</literal> "
"and <literal>product</literal> keywords."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1726
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"blacklist {\n"
"      device {\n"
"           vendor  \"DELL\"\n"
"           product \".*\"\n"
"       }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1733
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use a <literal>blacklist_exceptions</literal> section to enable "
"multipath for some devices that were blacklisted by the regular expressions "
"used in the <literal>blacklist</literal> section. You add exceptions by WWID "
"( <literal>wwid</literal> keyword), device name ( <literal>devnode</literal> "
"keyword), or device type ( <literal>device</literal> section). You must "
"specify the exceptions in the same way that you blacklisted the "
"corresponding devices. That is, <literal>wwid</literal> exceptions apply to "
"a <literal>wwid</literal> blacklist, <literal>devnode</literal> exceptions "
"apply to a <literal>devnode</literal> blacklist, and device type exceptions "
"apply to a device type blacklist."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1746
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, you can enable multipath for a desired device type when you "
"have different device types from the same vendor. Blacklist all of the "
"vendor’s device types in the <literal>blacklist</literal> section, and then "
"enable multipath for the desired device type by adding a <literal>device</"
"literal> section in a <literal>blacklist_exceptions</literal> section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1755
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"blacklist {\n"
"      devnode \"^(ram|raw|loop|fd|md|dm-|sr|scd|st|sda)[0-9]*\"\n"
"      device {\n"
"           vendor  \"DELL\"\n"
"           product \".*\"\n"
"       }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"blacklist_exceptions {\n"
"      device {\n"
"           vendor  \"DELL\"\n"
"           product \"MD3220i\"\n"
"       }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1770
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also use the blacklist_exceptions to enable multipath only for "
"specific devices. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1775
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"blacklist {\n"
"      wwid \".*\"\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"blacklist_exceptions {\n"
"        wwid \"3600d0230000000000e13955cc3751234\"\n"
"        wwid \"3600d0230000000000e13955cc3751235\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1792
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Following the reboot, the local devices should no longer be listed in the "
"multipath maps when you issue the <command>multipath -ll</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1798
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the <literal>find_multipaths</literal> option"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1799
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Starting with &productname; 12 SP2, the multipath tools support the option "
"<literal>find_multipaths</literal> in the <literal>defaults</literal> "
"section of <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> . This option prevents "
"multipath and <systemitem class=\"daemon\">multipathd</systemitem> from "
"setting up multipath maps for devices with only a single path (see "
"<command>man 5 multipath.conf</command> for details). In certain "
"configurations, this may save the administrator from needing to create "
"blacklist entries, for example for local SATA disks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1809
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Convenient as it seems at first, using the <literal>find_multipaths</"
"literal> option also has disadvantages. It complicates and slows down the "
"system boot, because for every device found, the boot logic needs to wait "
"until all devices have been discovered to see whether a second path exists "
"for the device. Additionally, problems can arise when some paths are down or "
"otherwise invisible at boot time&mdash;a device can be falsely detected as a "
"single-path device and activated, causing later addition of more paths to "
"fail."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1819
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>find_multipaths</literal> considers all devices that are listed in "
"<filename>/etc/multipath/wwids</filename> with matching WWIDs as being "
"multipath devices. This is important when <literal>find_multipaths</literal> "
"is first activated: Unless <filename>/etc/multipath/wwids</filename> is "
"deleted or edited, activating this option has no effect, because all "
"previously existing multipath maps (including single-path ones) are listed "
"in the wwids file. On SAN-boot systems with a multipathed root file system, "
"make sure to keep <filename>/etc/multipath/wwids</filename> synchronized "
"between the initial RAM disk and the file system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1831
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In summary, using <literal>find_multipaths</literal> may be convenient in "
"certain use cases, but &suse; still recommends the default configuration "
"with a properly configured blacklist and blacklist exceptions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1839
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring user-friendly names or alias names"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1841
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A multipath device can be identified by its WWID, by a user-friendly name, "
"or by an alias that you assign for it. Device node names in the form of "
"<filename>/dev/sdn</filename> and <filename>/dev/dm-n</filename> can change "
"on reboot and might be assigned to different devices each time. A device’s "
"WWID, user-friendly name, and alias name persist across reboots, and are the "
"preferred way to identify the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1851
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using persistent names is recommended"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1852
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Because device node names in the form of <filename>/dev/sdn</filename> and "
"<filename>/dev/dm-n</filename> can change on reboot, referring to multipath "
"devices by their WWID is preferred. You can also use a user-friendly name or "
"alias that is mapped to the WWID to identify the device uniquely across "
"reboots."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1861
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following table describes the types of device names that can be used for "
"a device in the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file. For an "
"example of <filename>multipath.conf</filename> settings, see the <filename>/"
"usr/share/doc/packages/multipath-tools/multipath.conf.synthetic</filename> "
"file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1870
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comparison of multipath device name types"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1877
#, no-c-format
msgid "Name Types"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1891
#, no-c-format
msgid "WWID (default)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1896
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The serial WWID (Worldwide Identifier) is an identifier for the multipath "
"device that is guaranteed to be globally unique and unchanging. The default "
"name used in multipathing is the ID of the logical unit as found in the "
"<filename>/dev/disk/by-id</filename> directory. For example, a device with "
"the WWID of <literal>3600508e0000000009e6baa6f609e7908</literal> is listed "
"as <filename>/dev/disk/by-id/scsi-3600508e0000000009e6baa6f609e7908</"
"filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1909
#, no-c-format
msgid "User-friendly"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1914
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Device Mapper Multipath device names in the <filename>/dev/mapper</"
"filename> directory also reference the ID of the logical unit. These "
"multipath device names are user-friendly names in the form of <filename>/dev/"
"mapper/mpath<replaceable>N</replaceable></filename> , such as <filename>/dev/"
"mapper/mpath0</filename> . The names are unique and persistent because they "
"use the <filename>/var/lib/multipath/bindings</filename> file to track the "
"association between the UUID and user-friendly names."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1929
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alias"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1934
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An alias name is a globally unique name that the administrator provides for "
"a multipath device. Alias names override the WWID and the user-friendly "
"<filename>/dev/mapper/mpath<replaceable>N</replaceable></filename> names."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1941
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are using user_friendly_names, do not set the alias to mpath "
"<replaceable>N</replaceable> format. This may conflict with an automatically "
"assigned user-friendly name, and give you incorrect device node names."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1953
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The global multipath <literal>user_friendly_names</literal> option in the "
"<filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file is used to enable or disable "
"the use of user-friendly names for multipath devices. If it is set to "
"<literal>no</literal> (the default), multipath uses the WWID as the name of "
"the device. If it is set to <literal>yes</literal> , multipath uses the "
"<filename>/var/lib/multipath/bindings</filename> file to assign a persistent "
"and unique name to the device in the form of <filename>mpath&lt;"
"<replaceable>N</replaceable>&gt;</filename> in the <filename>/dev/mapper </"
"filename> directory. The <literal>bindings file</literal> option in the "
"<literal>/etc/multipath.conf</literal> file can be used to specify an "
"alternate location for the <filename>bindings</filename> file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1968
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The global multipath <literal>alias</literal> option in the <filename>/etc/"
"multipath.conf</filename> file is used to explicitly assign a name to the "
"device. If an alias name is set up for a multipath device, the alias is used "
"instead of the WWID or the user-friendly name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1975
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the <literal>user_friendly_names</literal> option can be problematic "
"in the following situations:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1982
#, no-c-format
msgid "Root device is using multipath:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1984
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the system root device is using multipath and you use the "
"<literal>user_friendly_names</literal> option, the user-friendly settings in "
"the <filename>/var/lib/multipath/bindings</filename> file are included in "
"the <filename>initrd</filename> . If you later change the storage setup, "
"such as by adding or removing devices, there is a mismatch between the "
"bindings setting inside the <filename>initrd</filename> and the bindings "
"settings in <filename>/var/lib/multipath/bindings</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1994
#, no-c-format
msgid "Binding mismatches"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1995
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A bindings mismatch between <filename>initrd</filename> and <filename>/var/"
"lib/multipath/bindings</filename> can lead to a wrong assignment of mount "
"points to devices, which can result in file system corruption and data loss."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2002
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To avoid this problem, we recommend that you use the default WWID settings "
"for the system root device. You should not use aliases for the system root "
"device. Because the device name would differ, using an alias causes you to "
"lose the ability to seamlessly switch off multipathing via the kernel "
"command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2012
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mounting /var from another partition:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2014
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default location of the <literal>user_friendly_names</literal> "
"configuration file is <filename>/var/lib/multipath/bindings</filename> . If "
"the <filename>/var</filename> data is not located on the system root device "
"but mounted from another partition, the <filename>bindings</filename> file "
"is not available when setting up multipathing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2022
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that the <filename>/var/lib/multipath/bindings</filename> file is "
"available on the system root device and multipath can find it. For example, "
"this can be done as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:2041
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"defaults {\n"
"               user_friendly_names yes\n"
"               bindings_file \"/etc/multipath/bindings\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2052
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath is in the initrd:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2054
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Even if the system root device is not on multipath, it is possible for "
"multipath to be included in the <filename>initrd</filename> . For example, "
"this can happen if the system root device is on LVM. If you use the "
"<literal>user_friendly_names</literal> option and multipath is in the "
"<filename>initrd</filename> , you should boot with the parameter "
"<command>multipath=off</command> to avoid problems."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2062
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This disables multipath only in the <filename>initrd</filename> during "
"system boots. After the system boots, the <filename>boot.multipath</"
"filename> and <filename>multipathd</filename> boot scripts can activate "
"multipathing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2071
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipathing in HA clusters:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2073
#, no-c-format
msgid "See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-names-ha\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2080
#, no-c-format
msgid "To enable user-friendly names or to specify aliases:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2086
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file in a text editor with "
"&rootuser; privileges."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2092
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"(Optional) Modify the location of the <filename>/var/lib/multipath/bindings</"
"filename> file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2096
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The alternate path must be available on the system root device where "
"multipath can find it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Move the <filename>/var/lib/multipath/bindings</filename> file to <filename>/"
"etc/multipath/bindings</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the <literal>bindings_file</literal> option in the <literal>defaults</"
"literal> section of / <filename>etc/multipath.conf</filename> to this new "
"location. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:2114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"defaults {\n"
"          user_friendly_names yes\n"
"          bindings_file \"/etc/multipath/bindings\"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2124
#, no-c-format
msgid "(Optional, not recommended) Enable user-friendly names:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Uncomment the <literal>defaults</literal> section and its ending bracket."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Uncomment the <literal>user_friendly_names option</literal> , then change "
"its value from No to Yes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:2142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"## Use user-friendly names, instead of using WWIDs as names.\n"
"defaults {\n"
"  user_friendly_names yes\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2150
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"(Optional) Specify your own names for devices by using the <command>alias</"
"command> option in the <command>multipath</command> section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:2158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"## Use alias names, instead of using WWIDs as names.\n"
"multipaths {\n"
"       multipath {\n"
"               wwid           36006048000028350131253594d303030\n"
"               alias             blue1\n"
"       }\n"
"       multipath {\n"
"               wwid           36006048000028350131253594d303041\n"
"               alias             blue2\n"
"       }\n"
"       multipath {\n"
"               wwid           36006048000028350131253594d303145\n"
"               alias             yellow1\n"
"       }\n"
"       multipath {\n"
"               wwid           36006048000028350131253594d303334\n"
"               alias             yellow2\n"
"       }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:2179
#, no-c-format
msgid "WWID compared to WWN"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you define device aliases in the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</"
"filename> file, ensure that you use each device’s WWID (such as "
"<filename>3600508e0000000009e6baa6f609e7908</filename> ) and not its WWN, "
"which replaces the first character of a device ID with <filename>0x</"
"filename> , such as <filename>0x600508e0000000009e6baa6f609e7908</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2192
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save your changes, then close the file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After you have modified the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file, "
"you must run <command>dracut</command> <option>-f</option> to re-create the "
"<filename>initrd</filename> on your system, then restart the server for the "
"changes to take effect. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-conf-file-apply\"/"
"> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2208
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use the entire LUN directly (for example, if you are using the SAN "
"features to partition your storage), you can use the <filename>/dev/disk/by-"
"id/xxx</filename> names for <command>mkfs</command> , <filename>/etc/fstab</"
"filename> , your application, and so on. Partitioned devices have "
"<filename>_part&lt;n&gt;</filename> appended to the device name, such as "
"<filename>/dev/disk/by-id/xxx_part1</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <filename>/dev/disk/by-id</filename> directory, the multipath-mapped "
"devices are represented by the device’s <filename>dm-uuid*</filename> name "
"or alias name (if you assign an alias for it in the <filename>/etc/multipath."
"conf</filename> file). The <filename>scsi-</filename> and <filename>wwn-</"
"filename> device names represent physical paths to the devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:2227
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath device names in HA clusters"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2228
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that multipath devices have the same name across all devices by "
"doing the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2234
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use UUID and alias names to ensure that multipath device names are "
"consistent across all nodes in the cluster. Alias names must be unique "
"across all nodes. Copy the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf </filename> file "
"from the node to the <filename>/etc/</filename> directory for all of the "
"other nodes in the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2243
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using links to multipath-mapped devices, ensure that you specify the "
"<filename>dm-uuid*</filename> name or alias name in the <filename>/dev/disk/"
"by-id</filename> directory, and not a fixed path instance of the device. For "
"information, see <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-names\" xrefstyle="
"\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the <literal>user_friendly_names</literal> configuration option to "
"<literal>no</literal> to disable it. A user-friendly name is unique to a "
"node, but a device might not be assigned the same user-friendly name on "
"every node in the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:2261
#, no-c-format
msgid "User-friendly names"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you really need to use user-friendly names, you can force the system-"
"defined user-friendly names to be consistent across all nodes in the cluster "
"by doing the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2269
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file on one node:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the <literal>user_friendly_names</literal> configuration option to "
"<literal>yes</literal> to enable it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2278
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multipath uses the <filename>/var/lib/multipath/bindings</filename> file to "
"assign a persistent and unique name to the device in the form of "
"<filename>mpath&lt;<replaceable>N</replaceable>&gt;</filename> in the "
"<filename>/dev/mapper </filename> directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2286
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
