"the <filename> /sys/class/fc_transport/target*/node_name</filename> location."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:2462
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring failover priorities"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2463
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You must manually enter the failover priorities for the device in the "
"<filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file. Examples for all settings and "
"options can be found in the <filename>/usr/share/doc/packages/multipath-"
"tools/multipath.conf.annotated</filename> file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:2471
#, no-c-format
msgid "Understanding priority groups and attributes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2472
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <emphasis>priority group</emphasis> is a collection of paths that go to "
"the same physical LUN. By default, I/O is distributed in a round-robin "
"fashion across all paths in the group. The <command>multipath</command> "
"command automatically creates priority groups for each LUN in the SAN based "
"on the <literal>path_grouping_policy</literal> setting for that SAN. The "
"<command>multipath</command> command multiplies the number of paths in a "
"group by the group’s priority to determine which group is the primary. The "
"group with the highest calculated value is the primary. When all paths in "
"the primary group are failed, the priority group with the next highest value "
"becomes active."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2484
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <emphasis>path priority</emphasis> is an integer value assigned to a path. "
"The higher the value, the higher the priority. An external program is used "
"to assign priorities for each path. For a given device, the paths with the "
"same priorities belong to the same priority group."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2490
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>prio</literal> setting is used in the <literal>defaults{}</"
"literal> or <literal>devices{}</literal> section of the <filename>/etc/"
"multipath.conf</filename> file. It is silently ignored when it is specified "
"for an individual <literal>multipath</literal> definition in the "
"<literal>multipaths{)</literal> section. The <literal>prio</literal> line "
"specifies the prioritizer. If the prioritizer requires an argument, you "
"specify the argument by using the <literal>prio_args</literal> keyword on a "
"second line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: bridgehead
#: storage_multipath.xml:2500
#, no-c-format
msgid "PRIO Settings for the Defaults or Devices Sections"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2503
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>prio</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2505
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the prioritizer program to call to obtain a path priority value. "
"Weights are summed for each path group to determine the next path group to "
"use in case of failure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2510
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <literal>prio_args</literal> keyword to specify arguments if the "
"specified prioritizer requires arguments."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2514
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If no <literal>prio</literal> keyword is specified, all paths are equal. The "
"default setting is <literal>const</literal> with a <literal>prio_args</"
"literal> setting with no value."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:2519
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"prio \"const\"\n"
"prio_args \"\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2521
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example prioritizer programs include:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2531
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prioritizer Program"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2545
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>alua</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2550
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generates path priorities based on the SCSI-3 ALUA settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2557
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>const</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2562
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generates the same priority for all paths."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2569
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>emc</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2574
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generates the path priority for EMC arrays."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2581
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>hdc</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2586
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generates the path priority for Hitachi HDS Modular storage arrays."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2594
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>hp_sw</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2599
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Generates the path priority for Compaq/HP controller in active/standby mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2607
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>ontap</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2612
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generates the path priority for NetApp arrays."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2619
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>random</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2624
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generates a random priority for each path."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2631
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>rdac</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2636
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generates the path priority for LSI/Engenio RDAC controller."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2643
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>weightedpath</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2648
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Generates the path priority based on the weighted values you specify in the "
"arguments for <literal>prio_args</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2656
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>path_latency</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2661
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Generates the path priority based on a latency algorithm, which is "
"configured with the <literal>prio_args</literal> keyword."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: bridgehead
#: storage_multipath.xml:2673
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>prio_args</literal> arguments"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the arguments for the prioritizer programs that require arguments. "
"Most <literal>prio</literal> programs do not need arguments. There is no "
"default. The values depend on the <literal>prio</literal> setting and "
"whether the prioritizer requires any of the following arguments:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2683
#, no-c-format
msgid "weighted"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Requires a value of the form <literal>[hbtl|devname|serial|wwn]</literal> "
"<replaceable>REGEX1</replaceable> <replaceable>PRIO1</replaceable> "
"<replaceable>REGEX2</replaceable> <replaceable>PRIO2</replaceable> ..."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2691
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regex must be of SCSI H:B:T:L format, for example 1:0:.:. and *:0:0:., with "
"a weight value, where H, B, T, L are the host, bus, target, and LUN IDs for "
"a device. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:2696
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"prio \"weightedpath\"\n"
"prio_args \"hbtl 1:.:.:. 2 4:.:.:. 4\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2701
#, no-c-format
msgid "devname"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2703
#, no-c-format
msgid "Regex is in device name format. For example: sda, sd.e"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2709
#, no-c-format
msgid "serial"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2711
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regex is in serial number format. For example: .*J1FR.*324. Look up your "
"serial number with the <command>multipathd show paths format %z</command> "
"command. ( <command>multipathd show wildcards</command> displays all "
"<literal>format</literal> wildcards.)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2720
#, no-c-format
msgid "alua"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2722
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <literal>exclusive_pref_bit</literal> is set for a device ( <literal>alua "
"exclusive_pref_bit</literal> ), paths with the <literal>preferred path</"
"literal> bit set will always be in their own path group."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2731
#, no-c-format
msgid "path_latency"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2733
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>path_latency</literal> adjusts latencies between remote and local "
"storage arrays if both arrays use the same type of hardware. Usually the "
"latency on the remote array will be higher, so you can tune the latency to "
"bring them closer together. This requires a value pair of the form "
"<literal>io_num=<replaceable>20</replaceable> base_num=<replaceable>10</"
"replaceable></literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2741
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>io_num</literal> is the number of read IOs sent to the current path "
"continuously, which are used to calculate the average path latency. Valid "
"values are integers from 2 to 200."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2746
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>base_num</literal> is the logarithmic base number, used to "
"partition different priority ranks. Valid values are integers from 2 to 10. "
"The maximum average latency value is 100s, the minimum is 1&nbsp;&mu;s. For "
"example, if <literal>base_num=10</literal> , the paths will be grouped in "
"priority groups with path latency &lt;=1&nbsp;&mu;s, (1&nbsp;&mu;s, 10&nbsp;"
"&mu;s], (10&nbsp;&mu;s, 100&nbsp;&mu;s), (100&nbsp;&mu;s, 1&nbsp;ms), "
"(1&nbsp;ms, 10&nbsp;ms), (10&nbsp;ms, 100&nbsp;ms), (100&nbsp;ms, 1&nbsp;s), "
"(1&nbsp;s, 10&nbsp;s), (10&nbsp;s, 100&nbsp;s), &gt;100&nbsp;s."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: bridgehead
#: storage_multipath.xml:2760
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath Attributes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2761
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multipath attributes are used to control the behavior of multipath I/O for "
"devices. You can specify attributes as defaults for all multipath devices. "
"You can also specify attributes that apply only to a given multipath device "
"by creating an entry for that device in the <literal>multipaths</literal> "
"section of the multipath configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2770
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>user_friendly_names</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2772
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies whether to use world-wide IDs (WWIDs) or to use the <filename>/var/"
"lib/multipath/bindings</filename> file to assign a persistent and unique "
"alias to the multipath devices in the form of <filename>/dev/mapper/mpathN</"
"filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2778
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option can be used in the <literal>devices</literal> section and the "
"<literal>multipaths</literal> section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2803
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>no</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2808
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"(Default) Use the WWIDs shown in the <filename>/dev/disk/by-id/</filename> "
"location."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2816
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>yes</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2821
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Autogenerate user-friendly names as aliases for the multipath devices "
"instead of the actual ID."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2833
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>failback</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2835
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies whether to monitor the failed path recovery, and indicates the "
"timing for group failback after failed paths return to service."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2839
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the failed path recovers, the path is added back into the multipath-"
"enabled path list based on this setting. Multipath evaluates the priority "
"groups, and changes the active priority group when the priority of the "
"primary path exceeds the secondary group."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2866
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>manual</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"(Default) The failed path is not monitored for recovery. The administrator "
"runs the <command>multipath</command> command to update enabled paths and "
"priority groups."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2880
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>followover</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2885
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only perform automatic failback when the first path of a pathgroup becomes "
"active. This keeps a node from automatically failing back when another node "
"requested the failover."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2894
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>immediate</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2899
#, no-c-format
msgid "When a path recovers, enable the path immediately."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2911
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the path recovers, wait <replaceable>N</replaceable> seconds before "
"enabling the path. Specify an integer value greater than 0."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2920
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We recommend failback setting of <literal>manual</literal> for multipath in "
"cluster environments to prevent multipath failover ping-pong."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:2925
#, no-c-format
msgid "failback \"manual\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2928
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that you verify the failback setting with your storage system "
"vendor. Different storage systems can require different settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:2937
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>no_path_retry</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2939
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies the behaviors to use on path failure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2963
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal><replaceable>N</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2968
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the number of retries until <command>multipath</command> stops the "
"queuing and fails the path. Specify an integer value greater than 0."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2973
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In a cluster, you can specify a value of “0” to prevent queuing and allow "
"resources to fail over."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2981
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>fail</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2986
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies immediate failure (no queuing)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2993
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>queue</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:2998
#, no-c-format
msgid "Never stop queuing (queue forever until the path comes alive)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3006
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We recommend a retry setting of <literal>fail</literal> or <literal>0</"
"literal> in the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file when working "
"in a cluster. This causes the resources to fail over when the connection is "
"lost to storage. Otherwise, the messages queue and the resource failover "
"cannot occur."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:3013
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"no_path_retry \"fail\"\n"
"no_path_retry \"0\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:3016
#, no-c-format
msgid "Verification"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3017
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that you verify the retry settings with your storage system "
"vendor. Different storage systems can require different settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:3025
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>path_checker</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3027
#, no-c-format
msgid "Determines the state of the path."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3051
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>directio</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3056
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reads the first sector that has direct I/O. This is useful for DASD devices. "
"Logs failure messages in the &systemd; journal (see <xref linkend=\"cha-"
"journalctl\"/> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3065
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>tur</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3070
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Issues an SCSI test unit ready command to the device. This is the preferred "
"setting if the LUN supports it. On failure, the command does not fill up the "
"&systemd; log journal with messages."
msgstr ""

